
[1]finery

   FI'NERY, n.

   1. Show; splendor; gaiety of colors or appearance; as the finery of a
   dress.

   2. Showy articles of dress; gay clothes, jewels, trinkets, &c.

   3. In iron-works, the second forge at the iron-mills. [See Finary.]
